snippet.textDisplay:
* Overall energy efficiency: EV: 90%, Fuel Cell 30%
* Electricity is already everywhere, including your home.
* Solar makes even more sense when you have an EV.
* Hydrogen is generated from natural gas; electrolysis is just too expensive.
* You must fill your car at a gas station; most EV users charge at home when parked.
* Fuel cell cars must be serviced every 100k
* Fuel cell cars cost a $LOT$
* Fuel cells are less than 50% efficient; waste heat is the main product; compression, cooling & transport make up the rest of the waste.
